headline: Moderately bullish activity in Freeport McMoRan with shares up 2.39%
summary: Moderately bullish activity in Freeport McMoRan (FCX), with shares up $1.42, or 2.39%, near $60.63. Options volume relatively light with 15k contracts traded and calls leading puts for a put/call ratio of 0.56, compared to a typical level near 0.54. Implied volatility (IV30) dropped 0.79 near 53.88, in the highest 10% of observations over the past year, suggesting an expected daily move of $2.06. headline: Copper, Lithium, and Uranium Miners Delivered 127% While The S&P Returned 14%
summary: When investors buy a thematic ETF, they’re betting that a specific trend will reshape the economy. The Sprott Critical Materials ETF (NYSEARCA:SETM) takes that idea and applies it to the materials powering everything from electric vehicles to data centers to nuclear reactors.
